 The reason why it may appear that Goodluck Jonathan has an early advantage would be that he has control over the patronage resources  he has control to some extent over the media and outflow of information  so he ll use his considerable resources to make it appear as if he s the likely winner  I probably would not bet on that being the actual fact  Gire  I think I would agree with that assessment  In fact  my first thought when you floated that idea was that I didn t know that he was expected or favored to be the winner  On the contrary  many would argue that unless the ruling government does something underhanded he stands very little chance of winning the election  But to address specifically the issue of the Christian south controlling resources versus the Muslim  I think Nigeria is more nuanced than many people think  Not that long ago  if you remember  Moshood  Kashimawo Olawale  Abiola was said to have won what at that time  1993  were deemed the most free and fair elections in Nigeria s history  What is often lost is that fact that both Abiola and  Baba Gana  Kingibe were Muslim  so a Muslim Muslim ticket won overwhelming votes in Nigeria  It was General  Ibrahim  Babangida who nullified the election  in fact  that perpetrated a crisis referred to as June 12 that ultimately would lead to the presidency of Olusegun Obasanjo because it was deemed that Abiola being from the southwest was deprived and therefore the southwest was owed the presidency  So when Obasanjo in 1999 was contesting the politicians from the north  the party deliberately did not contest for the nomination  It was actually handed to them  What many people don t realize is that sometimes the general Nigerian public yearns for military intervention in the face of just reckless corruption with impunity as is happening just right now  Security is usually a very important issue for any country  and there has been insecurity for years  And there is a general perception  and I will argue a reality  that the current government has been unable to address or to effectively handle the problem  The impression therefore is that being a strong military leader  perhaps that s the kind of person that will be needed at this particular point in time to tackle the insurgency  Hentz  When the United States was getting ready to allow Japan to elect its own leaders to free it from its  United States  control and we were doing this because we wanted Japan to be a voluntary ally against the Soviet Union and the discussion was  well  Japan isn t ready yet  they ll probably choose an authoritative leader  And the response in Washington was  they need stability probably more than they need a Jeffersonian democracy  We in the West tend to think they  you  can telescope political development and think that you can get everything at once  I agree with James 100 percent  He may have been a dictator  but if he s elected  he s no longer a dictator he s an elected president first of all  and second of all the notion that he is a military man may resonate throughout the country and give them the stability that they need  I think it s frankly setting a bad precedent if Goodluck Jonathan does win  When he ascended to the presidency because the previous president died   I was in Nigeria at the time   and there were rumors of a coup d etat and instability because he was breaking the tradition of alternating northerners and southerners  and frankly it s probably a northerner s time to be the president  Gire  They call it the rotation of the presidency  When Jonathan insisted and got re elected  generally speaking including people like   President Obasanjo himself  say that he promised them that he was going to do just one additional term  So his now wanting to do another four years after doing six is viewed as breaking a promise  a solemn promise he had made  Copyright   2015 Virginia Military Institute  For academic and news media use only  No quotes from the materials contained herein may be used in any media without attribution to Virginia Military Institute  For other uses  contact Maj  Sherri Tombarge  540 464 7936  tombargesk vmi edu  Note  Transcripts are created on deadline  and accuracy may vary  This text may not be in its final form and may be updated or revised in the future  Please be aware that the authoritative record is the video  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Feb  14  Elections amid Unrest  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs Institute Writing Program Research Support Cadet Counseling Career Services Disabilities Services Miller Academic Center Advising Math Resource Center The Writing Center Resources Registrar Financial Aid Canvas Login Dean s Office Career Services Bookstore Cadet Computing Admissions Corps Life Athletics Library   Archives P